\section{Parsing all runs from a commit message}

A single commit message may contain multiple run blocks separated
by [[BLOCK_SEP]].
We split and parse each block, skipping any that don't start with
[[Run:]] (such as the initial commit message).

<<progsnap2 functions>>=
def parse_commit_runs(message):
    """Parse all run blocks from a commit message.

    Returns a list of dicts as produced by
    :func:`parse_run_block`.  Non-run blocks (like the
    initial commit) are skipped.
    """
    if not message or not message.strip():
        return []

    blocks = message.split(BLOCK_SEP)
    runs = []
    for block in blocks:
        stripped = block.strip()
        if stripped.startswith("Run:"):
            runs.append(parse_run_block(stripped))
    return runs
@

