\section{Extracting exception type and message}

The exception section of a run block contains a Python traceback.
The last line has the exception type and message, formatted as
[[ExceptionType: message]] or just [[ExceptionType]] when there
is no message.
We extract these for the [[X-ExceptionType]] and
[[X-ExceptionMessage]] custom columns.

<<progsnap2 functions>>=
def parse_exception_line(exception_info):
    """Extract type and message from exception info.

    Returns ``(exception_type, exception_message)`` where
    either may be ``None``.
    """
    if not exception_info:
        return None, None

    last_line = exception_info.rstrip().split("\n")[-1]
    if ":" in last_line:
        exc_type, _, exc_msg = last_line.partition(":")
        return exc_type.strip(), exc_msg.strip()
    return last_line.strip(), None
@

<<progsnap2 test functions>>=
def test_parse_exception_line_with_message():
    from learnlog.progsnap2 import parse_exception_line
    info = (
        "Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
        '  File "hello.py", line 1\n'
        "SyntaxError: invalid syntax"
    )
    typ, msg = parse_exception_line(info)
    assert typ == "SyntaxError"
    assert msg == "invalid syntax"

